Sentencas: The Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-delta triple-doped ceria (LSG) and triple-doped ceria-carbonate nanocomposites (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-delta - (Li-Na)(2)CO3) (LSG-LN) were prepared through sol-gel auto-combustion technique and followed by solid state mixing methods.
Titulo: Triple-doped Ceria-Carbonate (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-δ - (Li-Na)2CO3) nanocomposite solid electrolyte materials for LT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The characterization of prepared triple-doped ceria (LSG) and triple-doped ceria-carbonate nanocomposites (LSG-LN) (such as LSG, 85LSG-15LN, 75LSG-25LN, and 65LSG-35LN, respectively) was carried out by using X-ray diffraction (XRD), scanning electron microscopy (SEM), energy dispersive X-ray spectroscopy (EDS), Raman spectroscopy, impedance spectroscopy (IS), and the thermal expansion analyses.
Titulo: Triple-doped Ceria-Carbonate (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-δ - (Li-Na)2CO3) nanocomposite solid electrolyte materials for LT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: Sample formation, phase identification, surface morphologies and presence of elements in the prepared materials were analyzed with the help of XRD, SEM and EDS studies.
Titulo: Triple-doped Ceria-Carbonate (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-δ - (Li-Na)2CO3) nanocomposite solid electrolyte materials for LT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: The presence of oxygen vacancies and further structural analysis were investigated by the micro Raman spectroscopy.
Titulo: Triple-doped Ceria-Carbonate (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-δ - (Li-Na)2CO3) nanocomposite solid electrolyte materials for LT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: Totalionic-conductivity and activation energies in the temperature range from 250 to 600 degrees C were evaluated from the IS measurements.
Titulo: Triple-doped Ceria-Carbonate (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-δ - (Li-Na)2CO3) nanocomposite solid electrolyte materials for LT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: Thermal expansion analysis revealed the moderate values of coefficients of expansion in all the samples.
Titulo: Triple-doped Ceria-Carbonate (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-δ - (Li-Na)2CO3) nanocomposite solid electrolyte materials for LT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: Triple-doping with carbonate phase resulted in highest total-ion-conductivities i.e., 4.2 x 10(-1) S/cm and 4 x 10(-1) S/cm for 65LSG-35LN and 75LSG-25LN, respectively.
Titulo: Triple-doped Ceria-Carbonate (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-δ - (Li-Na)2CO3) nanocomposite solid electrolyte materials for LT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: Total-ion-conductivities of the triple-doped ceria-carbonate nanocomposite materials were found to be high when compared to the triple-doped ceria (i.e., 3.8 x 10(-2)
Titulo: Triple-doped Ceria-Carbonate (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-δ - (Li-Na)2CO3) nanocomposite solid electrolyte materials for LT-SOFC applications
Triple-doped Ceria-Carbonate (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-δ - (Li-Na)2CO3) nanocomposite solid electrolyte materials for LT-SOFC applications

Sentencas: Therefore, it is concluded that these triple-doped ceria-carbonate nanocomposite materials will be useful as a promising electrolyte in low temperature solid oxide fuel cell (LT-SOFC) applications.
Titulo: Triple-doped Ceria-Carbonate (Ce0.82La0.06Sm0.06Gd0.06O2-δ - (Li-Na)2CO3) nanocomposite solid electrolyte materials for LT-SOFC applications
